<br>
1.  The last think Christ told us was to &quot;Go and make disciples of all men.&quot;  If I believe He is the risen Son of God, I sure ought to do what he says.  And, though I am not perfect by any stretch, I try.<br>
<br>
2.  If there is one way to salvation, and I see many others going a different way, simply standing by and watching is pretty cold.  I cannot and will not try to make people believe anything, but it is my obligation to at least point out what I believe in the event it might make a difference to someone.  If I am all wrong, so be it.  If I am right, then &quot;interfering&quot; might have eternal consequences for someone.<br>
<br>
That said, I will point out that I only injected my thoughts here on what I think are a few simple points.  I did not, and do not, have any plans to make this a place for me to try to &quot;convert&quot; anyone.  I think this is a very unfruitful place to try to do that, and none of you have &quot;signed up&quot; for that.  We are simply folks who like the same game, and I will keep almost all my comments to that common interest.<br>
<br>
I just wanted to make my one point perfectly clear.  I think it does matter what we believe.  I cannot tell anyone what to believe.  I think the most dangerous thing is thinking it just does not matter. <p><font face=impact>

